      • getPotentialImports

        public abstract java.util.List<ImportJobDesc> getPotentialImports​(java.io.File location,
                                                                  java.lang.String folderPath)
        Returns a list of the potentially importable jobs in the given location.

        Note: The Job location is where the job's CJF will be placed, rather where its files will be placed. This can be different than the location passed to this method. It is assumed that the user will often select the incorrect location in which to perform the import (i.e. either one level above or one level below). To correct for this the potential imports should include more than those jobs that exist in the exact location specified.

        Parameters:
        location - a File referring to the location to import to
        Returns:
        a List of the importable job descriptions

      • isPropertyActive

        public boolean isPropertyActive​(java.lang.String propertyName)
        Description copied from interface: PropertyController
        Returns false if this object has a property with the given name that is considered inactive; otherwise true.

        The active active state of a property is separate from its enabled state to allow for optional properties that are actually a boolean paired with a property (i.e. value) of another type.

        Specified by:
